U.S. Political Figures COVID-19 Megathread
content:
This megathread is for discussing all news related to President Trump’s positive Covid-19 diagnosis and treatment, as well as positive test results from senators and other political figures related to the current outbreak.

​

**All discussion of this will be held here. As of now, several people have tested positive for Covid-19, including:**

President Donald Trump & Melania Trump

Senator Mike Lee (R-UT)

Senator Thom Tillis (R-NC)

Senator Ron Johnson (R-WI)

Bill Stiepen (Trump campaign manager)

Ronna McDaniel (GOP Chairwoman)

Hope Hicks (Trump political advisor)

Kellyanne Conway

Chris Christie

Nick Luna (Oval Office Operations Director & Trump's body man)

Kayleigh McEnany (White House press secretary) 

Chad Gilmartin (White House spokesman)

Karoline Leavitt (White House spokeswoman)

Admiral Charles Ray (U.S. Coast Guard second-in-command)

Jalen Drummond (White House spokesman)

Stephen Miller (White House Senior Advisor)

Rep. Salud Carbajal (D-CA 24th District)

​

Live updates:

[ABC News](https://abcnews.go.com/Politics/live-updates/trumpcoronavirus/?id=73402267)

[CBS News](https://www.cbsnews.com/live-updates/president-trump-covid-19-positive-test-latest-news-2020-10-04/)

[CNN](https://www.cnn.com/politics/live-news/trump-covid-19-updates-sunday/index.html)

[New York Times](https://www.nytimes.com/live/2020/10/02/world/covid-19-coronavirus#covid-trump-aides-politicians)

[Washington Post](https://www.washingtonpost.com/elections/2020/10/04/trump-covid-live-updates)

​

**Please remember all sub rules when commenting. Please be civil, and treat each other with respect. Thank you!**

​

October 3rd Updates:

[Chris Christie has checked himself into a hospital as a precaution](https://www.cbsnews.com/news/chris-christie-tests-positive-for-coronavirus/)

[Trump addresses the nation from Walter Reed medical center](https://twitter.com/realDonaldTrump/status/1312525833505058816?s=20)

[Nick Luna, director of Oval Office Operations and body man to Pres. Trump, has tested positive](https://twitter.com/ABC/status/1312599828061401088?s=20)

[Notre Dame president who attended Rose Garden event tests positive](https://www.cnn.com/2020/10/02/us/notre-dame-president-covid-trnd/index.html)

October 4th Updates:

[Trump’s medical team says he could be discharged from Walter Reed as soon as Monday. He reportedly experienced significant oxygen drops on Friday and Saturday](https://www.washingtonpost.com/elections/2020/10/04/trump-covid-live-updates)

[Reports that Trump didn't disclose a positive rapid test while awaiting a second, more thorough test on Thursday](https://www.wsj.com/articles/trump-didnt-disclose-first-positive-covid-19-test-while-awaiting-a-second-test-on-thursday-11601844813)

[Trump goes for drive outside Walter Reed medical center](https://twitter.com/Breaking911/status/1312869216954077186?s=19)

[Attorney General Bill Barr is now self quarantining](https://twitter.com/yasminv/status/1312871726108356608?s=20)

[White House says it will not release the number of staffers infected with coronavirus, citing privacy concerns](https://twitter.com/BNODesk/status/1312895849802932225?s=20)

[Biden tests negative for a second time](https://twitter.com/mviser/status/1312896046733950977?s=20)

[White House gives New Jersey officials the names of at least 206 individuals who may have been exposed to Covid-19 at a Trump fundraiser last week](https://twitter.com/NJDeptofHealth/status/1312837141907542016?s=20)

October 5th Updates:

[White House press secretary Kayleigh McEnany tests positive for coronavirus](https://www.cnn.com/2020/10/05/politics/kayleigh-mcenany-coronavirus-white-house/index.html)

[White House spokesman Chad Gilmartin tests positive for coronavirus](https://twitter.com/BNODesk/status/1313153897658306560?s=20)

[White House spokeswoman Karoline Leavitt tests positive for coronavirus](https://twitter.com/BNODesk/status/1313155682191978498?s=20)

[Trump tweets he will be leaving Water Reed today](https://twitter.com/realDonaldTrump/status/1313186529058136070?s=20)

[Trump leaves Walter Reed medical center and returns to the White House](https://youtu.be/_aNkToDMoGs)

October 6th Updates:

[Top U.S. military leaders, including the chairman of the Joint Chiefs of Staff, are quarantining after being exposed to the virus](https://www.nytimes.com/2020/10/06/us/top-us-military-leaders-including-the-chairman-of-the-joint-chiefs-of-staff-are-quarantining-after-being-exposed-to-the-virus.html)

[U.S. Coast Guard second-in-command, Admiral Charles Ray, tests positive for coronavirus](https://twitter.com/BNODesk/status/1313516416633647113?s=20)

[White House spokesman Jalen Drummond tests positive](https://twitter.com/BNODesk/status/1313578111028662277?s=20)

[White House Senior Advisor Stephen Miller tests positive](https://thehill.com/homenews/administration/519897-stephen-miller-tests-positive-for-coronavirus-reports)

[Rep. Salud Carbajal has tested positive](https://www.cnn.com/2020/10/06/politics/salud-carbajal-tests-positive-for-covid/index.html)

[Megachurch pastor who attended Rose Garden event tests positive](https://www.sacbee.com/news/coronavirus/article246262305.html)

[White House says they have completed contact tracing](https://www.cnn.com/2020/10/06/politics/white-house-contact-tracing-done/index.html)

[Secret Service Agents Frustrated With Trump's Unnecessary Coronavirus Risks](https://www.npr.org/2020/10/06/920849439/secret-service-agents-frustrated-with-trumps-unnecessary-coronavirus-risks)

October 7th Updates:

[White House doctor says Trump has been Covid symptom-free for 24 hours](https://www.theguardian.com/us-news/live/2020/oct/07/donald-trump-coronavirus-covid-19-white-house-kamala-harris-mike-pence-debate-joe-biden-live-updates)

[Trump insisting on working from Oval Office despite isolation rules, infection risks](https://abcnews.go.com/Politics/trump-insisting-working-oval-office-quarantine-rules-infection/story?id=73472757)

[Trump returns to Oval Office, says it's a "blessing from God" that he got COVID-19](https://www.cbsnews.com/news/trump-still-recovering-from-covid-19-returns-to-oval-office/)

[White House security official is gravely ill with COVID-19 since September](https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2020-10-07/white-house-security-official-contracted-covid-19-in-september)

October 8th Updates:

[Marine general has COVID after Pentagon meeting](https://apnews.com/article/virus-outbreak-archive-gary-l-thomas-coast-guard-59e19109d15d6f10eeb0417ec961d80d)

[Trump refuses to participate in virtual debate](https://www.cnn.com/2020/10/08/politics/second-presidential-debate-virtual/index.html)

​

*Click [here](https://www.reddit.com/r/Coronavirus/comments/j4j8m6/us_political_figures_covid19_megathread/?sort=confidence) to sort comments by Best.*

Scientific Studies Looking For Participants
content:
*What happened to the old post/Why did you guys make a new post? - Reddit automatically archives posts after 6 months, so we needed to make another post to keep it active in order to add studies*

With the rapid increase in severity of the coronavirus situation, we feel as though it is important to make a difference in any way we can. 

Therefore, we are calling on YOU, our users, to help scientists progress research!

**What does this mean?**

This post will host all of the studies/surveys for users to participate in. **Participation is strictly voluntary, and you may withdraw from any of the below studies at any time.** This post will be stickied to the r/Coronavirus subreddit whenever possible in order to give these projects ample exposure.

**For Researchers:** If you would like to have your study/survey posted, please [send us modmail](https://www.reddit.com/message/compose?to=%2Fr%2FCoronavirus) and we will give you instructions on how to verify your study.

In addition, there is a useful resource available for researchers from SafeGraph. They are sharing their data and that of their partners free for non-commercial and academic research use. To access this database, please [click here](https://www.safegraph.com/covid-19-data-consortium?utm_source=consortium_outreach&utm_campaign=consortium_rd)

**For Users:** Feel free to click on the links to any of the studies posted here that interest you and for which you qualify. Again, you are under no obligation to participate in any of the studies listed.


**Disclaimer:** All of the studies posted here have been verified to be authentic studies, either from a recognized research facility, government organization, or academic institution, and are conducted with all the necessary ethical and legal considerations. Individual studies may outline their specific disclaimers in the comments.

**NOTE: This post will remain active at all times. Please check back intermittently as we will be adding new studies on a regular basis. We may unpin the post from our front page to promote featured projects or AMAs, but we will re-pin it after the special events have ended. Individual comments with study details will be removed when the study has ended.**
